Class Song

Business.Entities.Song

public class Song
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Comparable<Song>
The type Song will be called everytime the user wants to access a song from the Database, or when downloading songs from the website.

      public Song​(int ID_song, java.lang.String title, java.lang.String composer, int duration, java.lang.String creation_date, java.lang.String copyright, java.lang.String genre, java.lang.String release_date, java.lang.String midi)
      Instantiates a new Song to be filled by the information from the Database.
      Parameters:
      ID_song - Int with the unique id from the song.
      title - String with the title from the song.
      composer - String with the composer from this song.
      duration - Int with the duration (in seconds) from the song.
      creation_date - String with the creation date from the song.
      copyright - String with the copyright from the song (Private/Public).
      genre - String with the genre from the song.
      release_date - String with the release date from the song.
      midi - String with the midi file containing the song, ready to be played by Sequencer.
